<item>
            <title>[THRIFT-2930] erlang module thriftTest_thrift referenced instead of thrift_test_thrift</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-2930</link>
                <project id="12310800" key="THRIFT">Thrift</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Both the &lt;tt&gt;lib/erl/README.md&lt;/tt&gt; as well as &lt;tt&gt;lib/erl/test/test_server.erl&lt;/tt&gt; mention a reference to &lt;tt&gt;thriftTest_thrift&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Running &lt;tt&gt;test_server:go()&lt;/tt&gt; will not fail until a client attempts to connect.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;make&lt;/tt&gt; creates the right modules and hrl files for &lt;tt&gt;thrift_test_thrift&lt;/tt&gt;,&lt;br/&gt;
and using this instead allows the client-server example in the README.md, to work as advertised.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
